## 2026-07-17 - US-006
- Implemented: fixed two bugs in `src/client-state.ts`'s unmerged-leaves join validation (RFC 9420
  SS7.9), extracting the logic from an inline block inside `validateRatchetTree` into a standalone
  exported `validateUnmergedLeaves(tree)` function so it's directly testable.
- Found this story's implementation already drafted, uncommitted, in the working tree at session
  start (`src/client-state.ts`, `test/index.ts` modified; `test/validation/unmerged-leaves-validation.ts`
  untracked). Reviewed it in full against the acceptance criteria before verifying and committing,
  same as the US-005 pattern.
- Files changed:
  - `src/client-state.ts`: (1) the "is this unmerged-leaf entry valid" check changed from
    `tree[nodeIndex]?.nodeType !== 'leaf' && !dp.includes(toNodeIndex(parentIndex))` to the same
    expression with `||` -- the old `&&` only rejected an entry when *both* the leaf was blank
    *and* it wasn't a descendant of the parent, so an entry satisfying only one of the two failing
    conditions (e.g. pointing at a blank leaf that happens to still be on the parent's direct path)
    was wrongly accepted. (2) the "every intermediate node on the path must also carry this leaf"
    check changed from `arraysEqual(dpNode.parent.unmergedLeaves, n.parent.unmergedLeaves)` (full
    array equality between two different nodes' entire unmerged-leaves lists) to
    `dpNode.parent.unmergedLeaves.includes(unmergedLeaf)` (membership of just the one leaf being
    checked) -- the old code wrongly rejected perfectly valid trees whenever two ancestors of the
    same leaf also each independently tracked other, different unmerged leaves, since the spec only
    requires each ancestor to list *that* leaf, not have an identical full set. Removed the now-
    unused `arraysEqual` import (the helper itself in `src/util/array.ts` is untouched/still used
    elsewhere).
  - `test/validation/unmerged-leaves-validation.ts` (new): two tests x every ciphersuite. (a) a
    4-leaf tree where leaf index 1 is unmerged under both its immediate parent (`unmergedLeaves:
    [1]`) and the root (`unmergedLeaves: [1, 3]`) -- different-but-overlapping lists -- asserting
    `validateUnmergedLeaves` returns `undefined` (previously falsely rejected by the `arraysEqual`
    bug). (b) a 2-leaf tree where the root claims leaf index 1 is unmerged but that leaf node is
    actually blank (`undefined` in the tree array) -- the leaf fails "non-blank" but trivially
    passes "is a descendant" (it's still on the direct path), so only one of the two conditions
    fails -- asserting `validateUnmergedLeaves` returns a `ValidationError` (previously wrongly
    accepted by the `&&` bug).
  - `test/index.ts`: registered the new validation test.
  - `specs/prd.json`: marked US-006 `passes: true` with notes.
- **Learnings for future iterations:**
  - Verified TDD properly despite the code already being drafted: `git stash push -- src/client-state.ts`
    (kept the test files), reran via the single-file esbuild-bundle recipe from Codebase Patterns.
    The pre-fix file doesn't even export `validateUnmergedLeaves` (the old code had the logic
    inlined directly in `validateRatchetTree`, not as a standalone function) -- so the bundle fails
    at build time with `No matching export in "src/client-state.ts" for import
    "validateUnmergedLeaves"`, which is a legitimate RED (the pre-fix code cannot satisfy the test
    at all, let alone incorrectly) rather than a runtime assertion failure. `git stash pop` restored
    the fix and all 57 assertions passed post-fix.
  - This is the second story in a row (after US-005) where a security-audit fix was already fully
    drafted uncommitted in the working tree at session start. Always run `git status`/`git diff`
    first before starting a story -- don't assume `passes: false` in `specs/prd.json` means no work
    exists yet; verify what's already there against the acceptance criteria instead of redoing it.
  - Full suite (`npm test`, 45405 assertions), `npm run lint`, and `npx tsc --noEmit -p .` (only the
    pre-existing, documented `test/test-vectors/key-schedule.ts` error, unchanged) all pass.
