    Add proposal accepted by group A itself first (sanity check that the honest path still works),
    then feeds that exact signed `PublicMessage` into group B's `processPublicMessage` and asserts it
    throws `ValidationError` -- this is the literal attack scenario named in the acceptance criteria.
  - `test/index.ts`: registered the new scenario test.
  - `specs/prd.json`: marked US-007 `passes: true` with notes.
