## 2026-07-17 - US-008
- Implemented: RFC 9420 SS12.4.3.2 validation of external-commit Remove proposals -- the receive
  path now rejects a Remove targeting an already-blank leaf (H5's missing `validateRemove` call),
  and binds an external-commit Remove to the joiner's own identity so a forged `new_member_commit`
  cannot evict an unrelated victim leaf (resync semantics).
- Found this story's fix already drafted, uncommitted, in the working tree at session start
  (`src/client-state.ts`, `src/process-messages.ts`, `test/index.ts` modified;
  `test/scenario/external-commit-unrelated-remove.ts` untracked) -- the fourth story in a row with
  this pattern (see the Codebase Patterns bullet above). Reviewed it in full against the acceptance
  criteria and SECURITY-AUDIT.md's H5 section before verifying and committing.
- Files changed:
  - `src/client-state.ts`: `applyProposals` gains an optional `newMemberLeafNode?:LeafNode`
    parameter. In the external-init branch, if the (at most one, per the pre-existing
    `validateExternalInit` check) Remove proposal is present, it now (1) runs `validateRemove`
    against `state.ratchetTree` (previously skipped entirely for external commits -- only member
    commits called this), and (2) looks up the removed leaf's node and throws `ValidationError`
    unless `newMemberLeafNode` is defined, the removed node is a non-blank leaf, and
    `constantTimeEqual(removedNode.leaf.signaturePublicKey, newMemberLeafNode.signaturePublicKey)`
    holds -- i.e. the Remove must target the exact leaf the new member itself previously occupied,
    identified the same way `defaultKeyPackageEqualityConfig.compareKeyPackageToLeafNode` (and
    `joinGroupExternal`'s own `resync`-leaf lookup in `create-commit.ts`) already establish "same
    identity" elsewhere in this codebase -- so the fix reuses an existing identity-comparison idiom
    rather than inventing a new one.
  - `src/process-messages.ts`: `processCommit` (the function shared by both
    `processPrivateMessage` and `processPublicMessage` -- see "Sender-side commit creation..." in
    Codebase Patterns for the shared-helper shape) now passes `content.content.commit.path?.leafNode`
    as `applyProposals`'s new `newMemberLeafNode` argument. A genuine external commit always carries
    an UpdatePath (its own new leaf's key material), so this is populated for every real external
    commit and `undefined` for member commits (where it's unused, since the Remove-binding branch
    only runs on the external-init path).
  - `test/scenario/external-commit-unrelated-remove.ts` (new): builds a group of alice + bob, then
    has an outsider "mallory" forge a `new_member_commit` external-join `PublicMessage` (via a new
    local helper, `forgeExternalCommitWithRemove`, that mirrors `joinGroupExternal`'s construction
    but -- unlike the real `resync` flag, which only ever targets the joiner's own former leaf --
    targets bob's leaf unconditionally) and asserts both alice's and bob's `processPublicMessage`
    reject it with a `ValidationError`, i.e. bob is never evicted by the forged commit. This is the
    H5 attack scenario verbatim (an external joiner evicting an unrelated victim).
  - `test/index.ts`: registered the new scenario test.
  - `specs/prd.json`: marked US-008 `passes: true` with notes.
- **Learnings for future iterations:**
  - Verified TDD properly despite the code being pre-drafted: `git stash push -- src/client-state.ts
    src/process-messages.ts` (kept the new test file and its `test/index.ts` registration), reran
    via the single-file esbuild-bundle recipe from Codebase Patterns -- got 38 failing assertions
    out of 76 pre-fix (roughly half the ciphersuites failed on "alice rejects the forged commit"
    with `t.ok(threw)` being `false`, i.e. the forged Remove was silently accepted; others failed
    differently, with `error.name` coming back as `InternalError` instead of `ValidationError` --
    both are legitimate pre-fix failures, just manifesting slightly differently depending on
    ciphersuite-specific tree/key details). `git stash pop` restored the fix; all 95 assertions in
    the new file passed post-fix across all 19 ciphersuites.
  - This is now the fourth story in a row (US-005 through US-008) where a security-audit fix was
    already fully drafted, uncommitted, in the working tree at session start -- the existing
    Codebase Patterns bullet on this already covers it, nothing new to add there.
  - `applyProposals`'s external-init branch only ever considers `grouped.remove.at(0)` (the single
    allowed Remove, already enforced by the pre-existing `validateExternalInit`'s "cannot contain
    more than one remove proposal" check) -- so the new identity-binding check doesn't need to
    handle a multi-Remove case; that's already structurally impossible by the time this code runs.
  - Full suite (`npm test`, 45557 assertions -- exactly the US-007 baseline of 45462 plus the 95 new
    assertions), `npm run lint`, and `npx tsc --noEmit -p .` (only the pre-existing, documented
    `test/test-vectors/key-schedule.ts` error, unchanged) all pass.
