  - `test/transcript-hash-epoch0.ts` (new): calls `nextEpochContext` directly with a fresh
    epoch-0 `GroupContext` (confirmedTranscriptHash empty, as `createGroup` produces) and asserts
    the resulting confirmedTranscriptHash equals `createConfirmedHash(new Uint8Array(), input, h)`
    -- i.e. derived from the empty interim hash, not from
    `createInterimHash(emptyConfirmedHash, confirmationTag, h)`.
  - `test/index.ts`: registered the new test.
  - `specs/prd.json`: marked US-013 `passes: true`.
- **Learnings for future iterations:**
  - `nextEpochContext`'s `confirmationTag` parameter is always the *previous* epoch's confirmation
    tag (`state.confirmationTag`, or `groupInfo.confirmationTag`/`gi.confirmationTag` at the
    call sites in create-commit.ts/process-messages.ts), used to derive
    `interim_transcript_hash[n-1] = Hash(confirmed_transcript_hash[n-1] || confirmationTag[n-1])`
    before folding in the new commit content to get `confirmed_transcript_hash[n]`. This is only
    valid for n-1 >= 1; for the very first commit (epoch 0 -> 1) RFC 9420 defines
    interim_transcript_hash[0] directly as empty, bypassing the Hash-based formula entirely (the
    epoch-0 confirmationTag computed in `createGroup` is used for the epoch-0 GroupInfo/Welcome
    confirmation tag itself, not for deriving a transcript hash input).
  - This story's existing `test/test-vectors/transcript-hashes.ts` (RFC test vectors) only
    exercises the primitives `createConfirmedHash`/`createInterimHash` directly with a given
    `interim_transcript_hash_before`, not `nextEpochContext`'s own chaining logic across epochs --
    it doesn't cover the epoch-0 special case, so a dedicated unit test against `nextEpochContext`
    itself was needed to RED/GREEN this bug (confirmed via `git stash`-style manual revert: without
    the fix the new test fails since `createInterimHash` hashes over a nonempty confirmationTag).
  - Full suite (`npm test`, 45585 assertions -- 45580 baseline + 5, one of which is this story's new
    assertion), `npm run lint`, and `npx tsc --noEmit -p .` (only the pre-existing, documented
    `test/test-vectors/key-schedule.ts` error, unchanged) all pass.
