## 2026-07-17 - US-014

- Implemented: `processMessage` (src/process-messages.ts) is the wireformat-dispatching entry
  point -- for `mls_public_message` it forwards the caller's real `pskIndex` to
  `processPublicMessage`, but for `mls_private_message` it was hardcoded to pass `emptyPskIndex`
  instead of the `pskIndex` parameter it already received, so any PSK proposal in a commit sent as
  a PrivateMessage would always fail PSK resolution (`ValidationError: Could not find pskId
  referenced in proposal`) even when the caller supplied a valid PSK index. Fixed by passing the
  real `pskIndex` through at process-messages.ts:438, and removed the now-unused `emptyPskIndex`
  import.
- Files changed: `src/process-messages.ts`, `test/scenario/psk-private-message.ts` (new),
  `test/index.ts` (wired in the new scenario file), `specs/prd.json` (US-014 passes:true).
- **Learnings for future iterations:**
  - The existing `test/scenario/external-psk.ts` calls `processPrivateMessage` directly, which
    bypasses `processMessage`'s wireformat dispatch entirely and therefore could never have caught
    this bug -- a story whose acceptance criteria is about a specific *wrapper/dispatch* function
    (`processMessage`) needs a test that calls that exact function, not just the inner function it
    delegates to.
  - `accumulatePskSecret` (src/psk-index.ts) throws `ValidationError('Could not find pskId
    referenced in proposal')` when `pskSearch.findPsk` returns undefined, so a PSK-index-not-wired-
    through bug gives a clean, unambiguous RED (thrown error) rather than a silent wrong-value --
    good signal for RED/GREEN verification without needing to inspect internal state.
  - `processMessage`'s signature is `(message, state, pskIndex, action, cs)` -- note `action`
    (an `IncomingMessageCallback`) has no default at this outer layer even though the inner
    `processPrivateMessage`/`processPublicMessage` default it to `acceptAll`; callers of
    `processMessage` directly must pass `acceptAll` (from `src/incoming-message-action.js`)
    explicitly.
  - Full suite (`npm test`, 45661 assertions -- 45580 baseline + 76 new PSK-scenario assertions
    from running across all ciphersuites), `npm run lint`, and `npx tsc --noEmit -p .` (only the
    pre-existing, documented `test/test-vectors/key-schedule.ts` error, unchanged) all pass.
