## 2026-07-17 - US-018
- Implemented: RFC 9420 SS12.1.6 requires every existing group member's LeafNode capabilities to
  support all extension types listed in a GroupContextExtensions proposal before that proposal can
  be accepted -- `validateProposals` (src/client-state.ts) now enforces this by walking
  `state.ratchetTree` (the pre-commit tree, i.e. "existing members") for every commit that contains
  a `group_context_extensions` proposal.
- Found this story's fix already drafted, uncommitted, in the working tree at session start
  (`src/client-state.ts`, `test/validation/proposal-validation.ts` both modified) -- the same
  recurring pattern documented in Codebase Patterns (now observed for the large majority of stories
  in this project). Reviewed the diff in full against the acceptance criteria and RFC 9420 SS12.1.6
  before verifying and committing, rather than assuming correctness or redoing the work.
- Files changed:
  - `src/client-state.ts`: in `validateProposals`, right after computing `allExtensions =
    flattenExtensions(p.group_context_extensions)`, a new guarded block (`if (allExtensions.length >
    0)`) walks every node in `tree` (the pre-commit `RatchetTree`) and rejects the proposal unless,
    for every non-blank leaf, one of: the leaf is being removed by a Remove proposal in this same
    commit (so it won't be a member once the commit applies -- mirrors the same remove-in-this-commit
    exemption `addsContainExistingKeypackage` already uses a few lines above), or
    `extensionsSupportedByCapabilities(allExtensions, leaf.capabilities)` holds (the same helper
    already used for `everyLeafSupportsGroupExtensions` -- Add vs current GroupContext extensions --
    and the `required_capabilities`-specific check further down in this same function). Returns a
    `ValidationError` otherwise.
  - `test/validation/proposal-validation.ts`: new negative-test block (immediately after the existing
    "can't use multiple group_context_extensions proposals" case, reusing the same `aliceGroup`
    fixture) builds a `group_context_extensions` proposal containing one made-up numeric extension
    type (9821, chosen to avoid the fixed GREASE reserved values in src/grease.ts and the empty
    default-capabilities extension list) and asserts `createCommit` throws `ValidationError`.
  - `specs/prd.json`: marked US-018 `passes: true` with notes.
- **Learnings for future iterations:**
  - Verified TDD properly despite the code being pre-drafted: `git stash push -- src/client-state.ts`
    (kept the test file), reran the isolated file via the single-file esbuild-bundle recipe from
    Codebase Patterns -- 19 failing assertions pre-fix (one "should have thrown ValidationError..."
    per ciphersuite), all 380 assertions in the file passing after `git stash pop`.
  - The check deliberately does NOT exempt the committer's own leaf -- the committer is as much an
    "existing member" as anyone else and must itself support any extension it proposes adding, so a
    solo-member group is already sufficient to exercise this check (no need to add a second member
    with deliberately-mismatched capabilities just for the test).
  - `extensionsSupportedByCapabilities`'s `isDefaultExtension` treats any *named* (string) extension
    type (e.g. `'external_senders'`, `'required_capabilities'`) as automatically supported regardless
    of a leaf's declared `capabilities.extensions` list -- only *numeric* (custom/unregistered)
    extension types are actually checked against the capabilities list. This is why the existing
    `group_context_extensions` proposal in `test/scenario/reject-incoming-message.ts` (extensionType
    `'external_senders'`) is unaffected by this new check, and why the new negative test needed a
    numeric, non-GREASE-colliding extension type to actually trigger a rejection.
  - Full suite (`npm test`, 45837 assertions -- 45818 baseline + 19 new), `npm run lint`, and
    `npx tsc --noEmit -p .` (only the pre-existing, documented `test/test-vectors/key-schedule.ts`
    error, unchanged) all pass.
