    same pattern as US-005/006/007/011/012/015/016/017/018 (see the Codebase Patterns bullet on this).
    The nontrivial part of reviewing it was confirming the epoch-0 exception isn't scope creep: grepped
    `src/resumption.ts` and found `reinitCreateNewGroup`/`branchGroup` both build a `PreSharedKeyID`
    with `psktype: 'resumption'` and `usage: 'reinit'`/`'branch'` and pass it as a PSK proposal into
    `createCommit` on a group that was *just* created by `createGroup` (so `groupContext.epoch` is
