    src/key-schedule.ts`) and got a real RED (both new assertions failed: `epochSecret` buffer was
    unchanged, not all zeros) across all 19 ciphersuites; `git stash pop` restored the fix and all
    57 assertions in the new file passed.
  - `Uint8Array.fill(0)` mutates the caller's buffer in place (it's a reference, not a copy) -- this
    is exactly what makes the wipe effective for `client-state.ts`'s
    `cs.rng.randomBytes(...)`-then-immediately-`initializeKeySchedule(...)` call site and for
    `deriveKeySchedule`'s freshly-`extractEpochSecret`'d buffer; both are otherwise-orphaned
    buffers with no other holder, so mutating them in place is safe.
